ce:section.ce:para:
The photocatalytic degradation of dyes was tested for PEA-PU-3T/M and PEA-3T/M membranes. From the result obtained (
                           Fig. S10
                        ), it can be seen that the Rh B solution treated with PEA-3T/M membranes remained light pink, with a significant amount of pink dye retained on the membrane surface. In contrast, the Rh B solution treated with PEA-PU-3T/M membrane became colorless and clear, with only a small amount of dye retained on the membrane surface. This phenomenon indicates that the PEA-3T/M membrane without PU adsorbed some dye molecules, due to the absence of hydrophilic sites caused severe aggregation of TiO2/MCD. This hindered the photocatalytic degradation of dye molecules by TiO2/MCD, resulting in membrane contamination and preventing the self-cleaning function. This result highlights the essential role of PU in enabling the membrane to achieve photocatalytic self-cleaning performance.
